          "body": "At 11:15 the seventh angel sounds, and loud voices in heaven announce the chapter's central proclamation: *the kingdom of the world has become the kingdom of our Lord and of His Christ; and He will reign forever and ever*. Note the **singular** kingdom — there has only ever been one kingdom; the question has been whose. The verb is **prophetic aorist** — the event is so certain that heaven speaks of it as already accomplished. The twenty-four elders fall on their faces (11:16) and thank God in language drawn from Psalm 2 and Daniel 7: God has *taken His great power and begun to reign* (11:17); *the nations were enraged, and Your wrath came* (11:18 — wordplay between *orgizo* and *orge*); the time has come for **judgment** of the dead, **reward** of the saints, and **destruction** of those who destroy the earth."
