          "title": "The opened temple — the covenant kept",
          "body": "The chapter closes (11:19) with the heavenly *naos* opened and the **ark of His covenant** appearing within. The ark — lost since 586 BC, never seen again in Israel, the subject of centuries of speculation — stands intact in heaven. The image is not archaeological but covenantal: every promise God has sworn (to Abraham, to Moses, to David, consummated in Christ) is **kept**. The accompanying flashes of lightning, thunders, earthquake, and hailstorm signal theophany — the same imagery as Sinai (Exodus 19:16-18) and the throne-room visions of Revelation 4:5 and 8:5. God has not forgotten His sworn word. The chapter ends with the believer's deepest confidence visible: the covenant ark, intact, in heaven, in the temple of the God who is and who was and who is to come."
